  "biography": "Mike Levine is an assistant professor of musicology at Christopher Newport University. His research utilizes ethnographic fieldwork conducted in Havana, Miami, and through digital platforms to investigate \u201cel paquete semanal\u201d (a popular USB-based internet platform in Cuba) and its relationship to improvised modes of informal music sharing and Cuban reparto music. He has written for \"Sounding Out!\", Hypermedia , Cuban Studies , Twentieth Century Music , and the volume Independence in 21st-Century Popular Music . He is currently drafting a monograph, Pegao: Underground Music and the Rise of Reparto in Post-Socialist Cuba , for University Press of Florida.",
  "education_entries": [
    "Ph D in Musicology, University of North Carolina - Chapel Hill",
    "MA in Musicology, City of University of New York - Brooklyn College",
    "MA in Music Technology, New York University - Steinhardt School of Education"
  ],
  "research_interests": "Cuban Music / Internet Studies / Popular Music",
